{
  "slug": "roast-pork-belly",
  "tutorialId": "cmp89vheq00006cv43x7aa8l4",
  "capturedAt": "2026-05-31T00:16:19.452Z",
  "preFix": {
    "title": "Roast pork belly",
    "subtitle": "Slow-roasted with shattering crackling",
    "excerpt": "Pork belly scored, dried overnight, then roasted low and slow before a blast of heat produces crackling that shatters. Rich, unctuous meat underneath.",
    "sourceNotes": "Standard British roast pork belly technique with two-stage oven method for crackling.",
    "body": {
      "type": "doc",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Pork belly is one of the most reliably satisfying Sunday roasts. The high fat content means it can be cooked for three hours at low heat without drying out. The crackling requires one piece of preparation that cannot be rushed: drying the skin uncovered in the fridge overnight.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "infoPanel",
          "attrs": {
            "tone": "tip",
            "title": "The drying step"
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "Good crackling comes from dry skin. Pat the pork dry after scoring, salt it generously. And leave it uncovered in the fridge for at least 8 hours. A damp skin steams rather than crisps.",
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": []
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "What you need",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "ingredientsList",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "name": "Pork belly",
                "unit": "g",
                "amount": 1600,
                "prepNote": "bone-in or boneless, skin scored at 1 cm intervals",
                "groupLabel": null,
                "isOptional": false,
                "ingredientId": "cmp49f49r002crkv4va5148iv",
                "ingredientSlug": "pork-belly"
              },
              {
